  "prompt": "Which is the best Android app locker?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" Android app locker can be subjective as it depends on your specific needs and preferences. However, several app lockers are highly rated and popular among users as of the latest updates. Here are a few you might consider:\n\n1. **Norton App Lock**: This is from the renowned security company Norton. It offers a simple interface and reliable protection using a PIN, password, or pattern to secure apps.\n\n2. **AppLock (by DoMobile Lab)**: This is one of the most popular app lockers with a wide range of features, such as fingerprint lock support, customizable themes, and the ability to lock system settings.\n\n3. **Smart AppLock**: This app not only locks apps but also provides options to lock settings, calls, and toggles for Wi-Fi and Bluetooth, adding an extra layer of security.\n\n4. **LOCKit**: Apart from app locking, LOCKit also offers features like photo vault, video vault, and notifications lock, giving it a multifunctional edge.\n\n5. **Security Master (by Cheetah Mobile)**: Previously known as CM Security, this app provides app locking features along with antivirus protection.\n\nWhen choosing an app locker, consider security features, user interface, ease of use, and additional functionalities that may be important to you. Always ensure that the app you choose is well-reviewed and regularly updated.",
